\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \ai\af0\afs18 \ltrch\fcs0 \i\f0\fs18\insrsid14183152\charrsid70890 The application of efaktur in the reporting of Periodic Value Added Tax (VAT) notification letters (SP
T) has a positive impact on company performance because making VAT returns is easier and shorter. However, the invoice system often encounters problems such as failure or rejection when uploading input or output invoices & incorrect data input due to an u
n
stable internet connection. This causes PT Siemens Indonesia's PT SPT reporting to be hampered, especially when reporting the company's VAT SPT. The purpose of this study is to analyze the implementation of the invoice system that can bring about changes 
a
t PT Siemens Indonesia in reporting VAT returns. Qualitative research is a research method used by the authors because the authors focus on the research and the objectives to be achieved, namely analyzing how the invoice system plays an important role in 
r
eporting VAT returns. The results of this study indicate that PT Siemens Indonesia has implemented it properly in fulfilling its tax obligations and there is no delay in reporting VAT returns. In terms of performance accuracy, as shown by comparisons befo
re and after using efaktur can save time because wet signatures are no longer used and replaced with electronic signatures listed on the efaktur display.}{\rtlch\fcs1 \ai\af0\afs18 \ltrch\fcs0 \i\f0\fs18\insrsid10976062\charrsid70890 
